    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse the<strong> quinoa</strong> in a sieve under<strong> cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with a lid with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and leave to steam-dry, uncovered, until serving</p>",
